AN: Total number of alleles in the dataset
DP: Total read depth at the variant site
FS: Phred-scaled p-value of Fisher's exact test for strand bias
MQRankSum: Z-score from Wilcoxon rank sum test of mapping qualities
ReadPosRankSum: Z-score from Wilcoxon rank sum test of read position bias
FractionInformativeReads: Fraction of reads informative about the variant
CLNDN: ClinVar disease name(s) associated with the variant
CLNDISDB: ClinVar database identifiers for associated conditions
CLNHGVS: ClinVar HGVS notation for the variant
CLNVCSO: Sequence Ontology term for variant type
GENEINFO: Gene symbol and Entrez Gene ID
ORIGIN: Origin of the variant (e.g., germline, somatic)
AD: Allelic depths for the reference and alternate alleles
AF: Allele fraction of the alternate allele
F1R2: Read counts supporting the alternate allele in forward orientation
F2R1: Read counts supporting the alternate allele in reverse orientation
RL: Repeat length of the inserted sequence
RU: Repeat unit of the inserted sequence
REPCI: Confidence interval for repeat copy number
CIGAR: CIGAR string representation of the variant
CIPOS: Confidence interval around the reported position
HOMLEN: Length of sequence homology at the breakpoint
HOMSEQ: Sequence of homology at the breakpoint
